The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, April 27: Indias fiscal deficit may come down to 5.21 per cent from the estimated 5.5 per cent of the GDP in the current fiscal on the back of higher revenues from the sale of 3G spectrum. The government has exuded confidence that revenues from 3G spectrum sale may touch Rs 50,000-55,000 crore from earlier expectations of Rs 35,000 crore.                             
	 Mumbai, April 27: Sebi has allowed stock exchanges to introduce derivative contracts such as futures and options on the volatility index. Meanwhile, it has directed Zenet Software to pay Rs 30.88 crore and barred it from trading in stock markets for a year for its alleged involvement in the IPO scam of 2003-05.                            
	 New Delhi, April 27: Taxpayers can now file their income tax returns easily with the government introducing Saral-II, the new income tax returns form, for assessment year 2010-11.                             
	 New Delhi, April 27: Essar Oil today said its promoters had infused over $293 million equity in the company by subscribing to global depository receipts issue.                            
	 New Delhi, April 27: The implementation of the new ground handling policy has been put off by the government till December 31.                                                                                                                          
